ls|ss|mb|p|mb|2c|mb|p|mb|?|at|Zia's rebid was 2@C. Fred and Zia had agreed to play that the bid of the 4th suit by an unpassed hand would be forcing to game, but they had not had any discussion about when a passed hand bids the 4th suit.|
pg| ***** 11 ***** |


hs|sc|mb|3c|nt|As such, Fred was not sure what Zia was up to with his 2@C call, but Fred's 3@C bid seemed like a good idea regardless of how Zia had intended 2@C. |
pg| ***** 12 ***** |


ls|sc|mb|p|mb|3d|mb|p|mb|?|at|Zia's next bid was 3@D. Fred presumed that Zia's hand was too good to bid a non-forcing 3@D on the round before. Fred, with a very solid opening bid, wanted to drive to game, but he was not sure if 3NT or 5@D would be better. |
